cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques to analyze the writing style of a specific person, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). It also involves social media analysis and information retrieval (cs.SI, cs.IR) to understand tweet popularity and generate excerpts of high-volume Twitter profiles. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of classifiers and models to compute characterization scores, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) or software engineering (cs.SD).
